The Prague Stock Exchange plunges into a minus against business closure.
After the steep fall in the morning, the Prague Stock Exchange was able to correct the losses.
Transactions with ČEZ shares reached almost half of the normal daily business.
At the very beginning of Tuesday ’ s business, the Prague Stock Exchange linked to Monday ’ s slump when it fell by another six percentage points.
This time the reason for the slump was Wall Street.
In the Czech Republic, too, the market ’ s reaction to the outcome of the vote by the American House of Representatives, which had refused to support a stabilisation plan for the financial sector there, is evident.
Case of shares in Asia
On Tuesday, the stock exchanges in Asia experienced a dramatic fall, although the indices were able to compensate for some of the losses during the day.
The Hang Seng index in Hong Kong lost almost four percentage points during the business day, but was able to compensate for some of the losses later, thus reducing the decline to about 2.5 percent.
The Hang Seng China Enterprises index, which observes the Chinese stock movement on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange, fell by 3.8 percent, while the markets in Shanghai were closed.
The shares on the Sydney Stock Exchange lost more than five percent, but then reduced losses to 4.3 percent.
The Taiwan stock exchange fell by 3.6 percent according to the local index.
"The timing of the US bailout is uncertain and will affect financial markets around the world," said Joseph Yam, the chief monetary authority in Hong Kong.
Hong Kong, although it belongs to China, determines its own monetary policy, regardless of the central bank of China.
Interest rates in Hong Kong are at the same level as those in the United States.
According to Australian Prime Minister Kevin Rudd, American legislators should return to the negotiating table as soon as possible and adopt the draft support for the financial system.
Otherwise, other countries would also be affected by the collapse.
A bloodbath of American shares
On Monday, the American House of Representatives rejected the plan to support the financial system, for which up to $700 billion (nearly $12 trillion) should be spent.
The legislators thus ignored President George Bush ’ s call to support the plan.
Bush ’ s view is that the plan would regulate the underlying causes of the financial crisis and thus help stabilize the entire economy.
On Monday, America ’ s shares had a bloodbath, and the main equity indices recorded the largest slump in more than 20 years.
The Dow Jones index fell by almost seven percent, with a similar slump last recorded in 1987.
The index had already fallen before the vote, but there was hardly any evidence that the draft would not get through in the House of Representatives.
Congress Confessions: US government allowed to pump $700 billion into banks
The top representatives of the American Congress and the administration of President George W. Bush have agreed on a broader form of agreement on financial assistance to the American financial system.
This is to be voted on early next week.
American legislators achieved a breakthrough in talks on the adoption of a bailout in the form of financial assistance to the US financial system of $700 billion (about 12 trillion crowns).
However, this does not mean victory.
Congressmen must negotiate some details of the agreement before they can publish and vote on the final version of the law.
The plan to support the financial system will be negotiated in the US Congress on Monday.
On Sunday, the chairman of the Committee on Banking and Financial Services Barney Frank told the Reuters agency.
According to different data, the Senate could probably vote on the plan at the earliest on Wednesday.
According to economists, a communication that the plan is being adopted should be the first major psychological factor in stimulating financial markets.
After that, however, there was a 'disillusionment' due to the complicated mechanisms of how to help markets in practice.
Paulson: The plan must be effective
"We have made significant progress.
We have clarified our different views on what a package should look like to stabilise the market, "said Nancy Pelosi, a democrat with the Bloomberg agency.
They say that a final vote could take place on Sunday.
Representatives of legislators met with US Treasury Secretary Henry Paulson on Sunday night to give the government fund its final form.
This provides for a purchase of unsaleable mortgage assets from the financial companies, which plunge financial firms into serious losses and jeopardise the stability of the entire system.
"We are on the verge of a definitive agreement on a plan that will work and which must also be effective on the market.
The recovery plan needs to be continued, but I think we are at the end ", says Paulson.
A signal for Asian business
The global financial crisis is also reflected in the stock markets, which are falling sharply.
According to the words of Nevada ’ s Democratic Senator Harry Reid, legislators are trying to reach a final agreement before Sunday in Congress.
This is because it is intended to reassure investors of business in Asian financial markets, which are in the first time zone where a Congress decision could affect business on Monday.
So far, however, it is not yet quite clear when both chambers of the American Congress will vote on the law, and there is also uncertainty as to whether the negotiations could fail at the last minute due to a problem.
The legislators hope that it will be adopted in the next few days.
The law, however, will undergo some changes.
The total amount intended to assist the system is to be divided into two parts.
The initial $350 billion will be made available as soon as possible, as President George Bush called for.
But Congress can block the distribution of the remaining money if it feels that the program does not fulfil its function, with another $100 billion, and later with the final $350 billion.
Bush favours progress in negotiations
The President has a veto right in this decision, but Congress can overrule its veto.
Despite these changes, however, the basic idea of the program has remained based on obtaining finance for the purchase of bad mortgage securities whose value has fallen, because hundreds of thousands of Americans are no longer able to repay their mortgages.
"We have worked out everything.
The House of Representatives should be able to vote on the law on Sunday, the Senate then on Monday, "said Republican Senator Judd Gregg.
American President Bush was also satisfied with the progress.
His spokesman, Tony Fratto, said that Bush was satisfied with Saturday ’ s progress and “appreciated the two-way effort to stabilize our financial markets and protect our economy. ”
Limitation of golden parachutes
The Chairman of the Senate Banking Committee Christopher Dodd, the senior negotiator, said that the legislators had agreed on a responsibility for the monetary programme, the protection of taxpayers from losses, the conclusion of benefits and a timetable for financing the plan.
The new law should also restrict the so-called golden parachutes for directors of the companies involved in the programme and establish a committee to which the supervision of the fund is to be entrusted.
This is to be managed by the Ministry of Finance.
"We have worked very hard and achieved great progress towards an agreement that works and is important for the market and for all Americans," said Paulson.
The plan also expects help for homeowners who have problems repaying their mortgage.
The government should negotiate new rates on mortgages it buys, with the aim of reducing the monthly costs for debtors and enabling them to keep their homes.
Marek: Psychological aid
The proposed plan is a good idea, according to Patria Finance ’ s chief economist David Marek, but implementation will be very difficult.
"This is because one does not know by what mechanism and at what price the problematic assets are bought up.
This will be crucial to how the financial sector and the government divide the losses, "said Marek to the iHNed.cz.
Whether the plan is adopted now or early next week is not decisive, Marek believes.
"It is much more important that congressmen agree to support the plan and adopt it as soon as possible.
The psychological importance of the agreement on adoption is the most important thing at this moment, "Marek stressed.
