The drivers, who can be relapsed because of the alcohol level, will have to install the 'Alcolock'.
The authority orders that the driver, who had three official penalties for the alcohol level, installs in his car this system, which forbids him to start the car in a drunken state. If he is alcoholized, then the car does not start.
The initiative was announced last month in June and is already part of the report of the Prosecutor General ’ s Office. According to her, it is a pilot ’ s project, which will last for a year.
The purpose is to rehabilitate the driver, which is why he gets a course for the re-education of traffic behaviour.
In addition to the Prosecutor General ’ s Office, the Ministry of Transport and the Foundation of the Technical Institute for Automotive Safety will also participate.
According to statistics, between 30 and 75% of drivers, who were reported more than once because of driving under alcohol influence, sat back at control.
The 'alcolock' would prevent this because it is a system connected to the car, it measures the alcohol content in the exhausted air and prevents autostart when the driver has made alcohol test; or if an alcohol concentration is detected which is higher than permitted.
It costs more than EUR 1 000, the costs are borne by the person who imposes the sanction.
In this context, a study conducted in the US in 2007 has shown that cars equipped with these devices will prevent up to 65% of breaches in the first year after its introduction.
In Spain, it is expected that 115 lives could be saved annually.
The measure is limited to administrative sanctions for two reasons: to tackle this behaviour before it becomes a crime.
And in order to facilitate their implementation, a regular reform can be carried out in the ordinary way, and yet a reform of the Basic Law, which is necessary for the law enforcement process, is required.
The device is not yet available in Spanish markets, even though it has already been installed in some commercial vehicles and public transport vehicles.
Tomorrow, the House of Representatives will vote because of the initiative of the Spanish Socialist Workers ’ Party, which proposes to install this system in school buses. This has already been done in France.
